<% content_for(:page_title, "Hello") %>

<main>
  <section class="background background--python-logo
    background--light-gradient-cover-bottom-half">
      <div class="media-object page-header">
        <%= image_tag("marketing/python-logo.svg",
              class: "page-header__offset-image") %>

        <div>
          <h1 class="page-header__title python">
            Python & Django
          </h1>

          <h2 class="u-margin-bottom-medium">
            You want it? We'll make it.
          </h2>

          <p class="page-header__intro u-margin-bottom-large">
            We have experts Developers ready to share the ins-and-outs of Python
            &amp; Django with you.  Sign up for our pre-launch and <mark>get 25%
            off your first month of Upcase.</mark>
          </p>

          <a href="#sign-up" class="button">
            Sign me up for the pre release!
          </a>
        </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section page-section--dark">
    <div class="page-content">
      <h1 class="u-margin-bottom-medium">
        Proposed Classes*
      </h1>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Installing Python & Django
            </h2>

            <p>
              This is a video in which we walk through the many details of
              setting up a computer with Django running.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Creating a Custom User Model
            </h2>

            <p>
              In this exercise we implement a story: As a user I want to sign up
              using my email addresses and a password. I don't like password
              confirmation fields.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Fix The Build By Adding a User Signs In Feature
            </h2>

            <p>
              Download a repo containing a Django app with failing tests.
              Implement a user story to make the tests pass.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Forms and Django Structure
            </h2>

            <p>
              A video in which we describe the anatomy of a Django app, and walk
              through how forms work by test-driving a form submission and
              confirmation screen.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Uploading to S3
            </h2>

            <p>
              In this video we start to work with S3 attachments: how to set it
              up, and then detail on how S3 interacts with Django forms.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Creator Creates a Zine
            </h2>

            <p>
              An exercise where we implement this story: As a creator I want to
              upload a zine (PDF) to the service. The PDF itself goes to S3, the
              metadata goes to the Django app.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              The Manager
            </h2>

            <p>
              This is a video in which we show all the cool things you can do
              with the ORM manager, including multiple managers, raw SQL,
              complex queries.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Filtering Zines
            </h2>

            <p>
              In this exercise we add this functionality:

              <ul class="u-margin-bottom default-list">
                <li>
                  A list of all the zines (/zines).
                </li>
                <li>
                  Search on zine creator name (/zines?author=?).
                </li>
              </ul>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Following Authors
            </h2>

            <p>
              We build a dashboard page with a list of all zines from creators
              they follow, to satisfy this story: As a reader I want to
              subscribe to a creator so that I can know more easily when they
              publish new work.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card u-margin-bottom-medium">
        <div class="card__content media-object media-object--top-down">
          <span class="dot"></span>

          <div>
            <h2 class="u-margin-bottom">
              Wrapping Up
            </h2>

            <p class="u-margin-bottom">
              A quick summary of what we've learned and some jokes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="reading u-margin-bottom-large">
        * The actual class structure may vary slightly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="sign-up" class="background background--upcase-logo-dark
    background--light-gradient-cover-top-half">
    <div class="page-content">
      <div class="card card--narrow">
        <div class="card__content">
          <h2 class="card__heading">
            Learn Python & Django with the experts at Upcase
          </h2>

          <p class="card__copy">
            Sign up for our pre-launch and <mark>get 25% off your first month of
            Upcase</mark>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card__content card__content--dark">
          <form accept-charset="UTF-8"
            action="https://formkeep.com/f/9baea90e4fc2" method="POST">
            <input type="hidden" name="utf8" value="âœ“">
            <label for="email-address">Email Address</label>
            <div class="single-line-form">
              <input type="email" name="email" class="single-line-form__input">
              <input type="hidden" name="language" value="Python & Django">
              <button class="button button--on-dark single-line-form__button" type="submit">
                Add me to the list
              </button>
            </div>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
